127 SECTION 2.
128 Said chapter is further amended by revising Code Section 2-23-9.1, relating to consumable
129 hemp products, certificate of analysis, THC warning, and inspections, as follows:
130 "2-23-9.1.
131 (a) No consumable hemp product shall be sold or otherwise distributed in this state if such
132 product has a total concentration of THC and other intoxicating cannabinoids that exceeds
133 0.3 percent, determined on a dry weight basis where applicable.
134 (b) No consumable hemp product shall be sold or otherwise distributed in this state unless
135 the processor or manufacturer has, within the last 12 months, contracted for a full panel
136 certificate of analysis to be conducted on such product and such analysis has been
137 conducted and made available to the public. Such full panel certificate of analysis shall,
138 at a minimum:
139 (1) Attest to the presence and amount, in such product's final packaged form, of the
140 following compounds or groups of compounds:
141 (A) THC and other intoxicating cannabinoids;
142 (B) Cannabidiol (CBD);
143 (C) Cannabidiolic acid (CBDA);
144 (D) Cannabigerol (CBG);
145 (E) Cannabigerolic acid (CBGA); and
146 (F) Cannabinol (CBN);
