184 SECTION 3.
185 Said chapter is further amended in Code Section 2-23-9.2, relating to consumable hemp
186 products, packaging, and advertising, by revising subsection (c) as follows:
187 "(c)(1) As used in this subsection, the term:
188 (A) 'Food product' means any product intended to be consumed by humans for physical
189 subsistence; provided, however, that such term shall not include products that constitute
190 drinks or beverages.
191 (B) 'Gummy' means a gelatinous substance in the form of a cube, sphere, prismatoid,
192 ovoid, or other shape that is designed for human ingestion.
193 (2) No consumable hemp product shall be sold or otherwise distributed in this state if
194 such product constitutes or is a component of:
195 (A) A food product; or
196 (B) A drink or beverage that contains alcohol or constitutes an alcoholic beverage
197 under Title 3.
